  "prompt": "Is erectile dysfunction treatable or not?",
  "response": "Yes, erectile dysfunction (ED) is treatable. There are several treatment options available:\n\n1. Medications:\n- Oral medications like Viagra, Cialis, and Levitra\n- PDE5 inhibitors\n\n2. Lifestyle changes:\n- Regular exercise\n- Healthy diet\n- Weight management\n- Reducing alcohol consumption\n- Quitting smoking\n\n3. Psychological treatments:\n- Counseling\n- Stress management\n- Treatment for anxiety or depression\n\n4. Medical procedures:\n- Hormone therapy\n- Penile implants\n- Vacuum erection devices\n- Injections\n\n5. Addressing underlying health conditions:\n- Treating diabetes\n- Managing cardiovascular issues\n- Controlling blood pressure\n\n6. Alternative therapies:\n- Acupuncture\n- Herbal supplements (consult a doctor first)\n\nThe effectiveness of treatment depends on the underlying cause of ED. Many men see improvement with a combination of medical treatments and lifestyle modifications. Consulting a healthcare professional is recommended to determine the most appropriate treatment approach.",
